Attack Scenarios

For Lecture 1 & 2

 

“Node S” does not forward data of “Source node”. Which type is of node “S”?

 

Selfish Node

 

Which type of tool is used by Monitoring PC?

 

Sniffer

 

“Node M” drops all the data packets. Which type is of “node M”?

 

Malicious node

 

Which type of attack is this?

 

Snooping

 

A device is used by attacker so that the user is getting a noisy signal. Which type of attack is this?

 

Communication Jamming

 

The attacker is secretly listening to the conversation. Which type of attack is this?

 

Eavesdropping

 

The actual link is not used. The data goes through an attacker. What can we call this attacker?

 

Man in the Middle

 

The hacker is changing the actual message.

 

Message Modification

 

The attacker is sending too many requests to the server. What type of attack is this?

 

Denial of Service

 

Darth pretends that he is Bob.

 

Masquerading

 

Attacker is using many systems. All the systems are sending too many requests to the server at the same time.

 

Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS)
